main event: A newspaper reporter observed an object traveling at a high rate of speed, having intense brilliance, without appearance of any known aircraft in Aguadulce, Panama.
interesting points: The sighting was reported on 10 January 1953 but documented later in January,The object was seen as not being a conventional aircraft, with no physical evidence found,The report was made by a reliable observer who is not considered subject to hallucinations,The incident was deemed important enough to warrant further investigation,Two newspaper clippings were included in the original report.
